{"title":"The Original Off-Road Adventure Saddle: Springy Brooks B72 is Back in Production","link":"https://bikerumor.com/brooks-b72-leather-spring-saddle-back-in-production/","date":1701446334000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1280\" height=\"720\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-on-bike-lean.jpeg\" alt=\"Brooks England B72 on bike lean\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-on-bike-lean.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-on-bike-lean-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-on-bike-lean-800x450.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-on-bike-lean-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-on-bike-lean-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-on-bike-lean-1200x675.jpeg 1200w\" /></p>\n<p>Since 1866, <a href=\"https://www.brooksengland.com/en_us/\">iconic bicycle saddle maker</a>, Brooks England has been producing bike saddles. In that time they’ve removed and added different models. Today, they announced that they brought back the B72 to their leather line-up. And the <a href=\"https://www.brooksengland.com/en_us/b72.html\">iconic, early MTB saddle</a> is available now. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-old-school-mtb-e1701287268912.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"577\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-old-school-mtb-e1701287268912-800x577.jpg\" alt=\"Brooks England B72 old school mtb\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-old-school-mtb-e1701287268912-800x577.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-old-school-mtb-e1701287268912-297x214.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-old-school-mtb-e1701287268912-120x87.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-old-school-mtb-e1701287268912-768x554.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-old-school-mtb-e1701287268912.jpg 1197w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Brooks England)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Wait, how long have they been making saddles? Let’s do the math, 2023 minus 1866, carry the one… jeez… Brooks has been producing bike saddles for 157 years. That’s a long time, kids. I’d go out on a limb and say that they know a thing or two about manufacturing a quality leather bike saddle.  </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>The Brooks B72</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-studio-from-the-back-e1701287131483.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"400\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-studio-from-the-back-e1701287131483-800x400.jpeg\" alt=\"Brooks England B72 studio from the back\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-studio-from-the-back-e1701287131483-800x400.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-studio-from-the-back-e1701287131483-297x149.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-studio-from-the-back-e1701287131483-120x60.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-studio-from-the-back-e1701287131483-768x384.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-studio-from-the-back-e1701287131483.jpeg 1000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-studio-from-the-side-e1701287151189.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"413\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-studio-from-the-side-e1701287151189-800x413.jpeg\" alt=\"Brooks England B72 studio from the side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-studio-from-the-side-e1701287151189-800x413.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-studio-from-the-side-e1701287151189-297x153.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-studio-from-the-side-e1701287151189-120x62.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-studio-from-the-side-e1701287151189-768x396.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-studio-from-the-side-e1701287151189.jpeg 1000w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-under-carriage-e1701287180228.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"549\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-under-carriage-e1701287180228-800x549.jpeg\" alt=\"Brooks England B72 under carriage\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-under-carriage-e1701287180228-800x549.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-under-carriage-e1701287180228-297x204.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-under-carriage-e1701287180228-120x82.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-under-carriage-e1701287180228-768x527.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-under-carriage-e1701287180228.jpeg 1000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Brooks first launched the B72 way back in the 1930’s. Its refined loop suspension helped add a touch of comfort for the upright cyclist who gravitated “toward unhurried touring”. It was lighter than other sprung saddles, and it became the saddle of choice for road tourers and old-school MTB riders. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-Outta-the-saddle.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-Outta-the-saddle-800x450.jpeg\" alt=\"Brooks England B72 Outta the saddle\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-Outta-the-saddle-800x450.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-Outta-the-saddle-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-Outta-the-saddle-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-Outta-the-saddle-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-Outta-the-saddle-1200x675.jpeg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-Outta-the-saddle.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As mentioned before, the B72 played a big part in the birth of mountain biking. Back before the days of full suspension and plastic… err, I mean, carbon-fiber frames, there were some daredevil hippies out there riding their bikes off-road, exploring the terrain and the limits of their (often pieced together) steeds. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-from-the-rear.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-from-the-rear-800x450.jpeg\" alt=\"Brooks England B72 from the rear\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-from-the-rear-800x450.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-from-the-rear-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-from-the-rear-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-from-the-rear-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-from-the-rear-1200x675.jpeg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-from-the-rear.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Brooks B72 saddle was the top choice of the cyclists who built the sport and stood up to the demands of those mountain bike pioneers. Equipped with a dual-rail, the B72 uses the shock-damping loop suspension that made it a fixture at early MTB races and rides. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-on-a-bike-from-the-side.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-on-a-bike-from-the-side-800x450.jpeg\" alt=\"Brooks England B72 on a bike from the side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-on-a-bike-from-the-side-800x450.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-on-a-bike-from-the-side-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-on-a-bike-from-the-side-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-on-a-bike-from-the-side-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-on-a-bike-from-the-side-1200x675.jpeg 1200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-on-a-bike-from-the-side.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Today, this saddle would be great for that perfect finishing touch on a vintage Klunker restoration project. Or as a saddle for a modern ATB bike, like say, my <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/rivendell-gus-boots-willsen-hillibike-review/\">Rivendell Gus Boots Willsen</a>. It would also be great for a long-distance touring bike or a bike used for adventurous city exploring, allowing you to do so in comfort and style. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-studio-with-packaging-e1701287199638.jpeg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"688\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-studio-with-packaging-e1701287199638-800x688.jpeg\" alt=\"Brooks England B72 studio with packaging\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-studio-with-packaging-e1701287199638-800x688.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-studio-with-packaging-e1701287199638-297x255.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-studio-with-packaging-e1701287199638-120x103.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-studio-with-packaging-e1701287199638-768x660.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Brooks-England-B72-studio-with-packaging-e1701287199638.jpeg 1000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The saddle uses tubular rivets in its construction, as well as a vegetable-tanned leather top, and a twin-rail steel frame. the B72 is ideal for casual touring, upright cycling in the city, and for use with classic bicycles. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you register your new saddle within 3 months of the date of purchase, Brooks will extend the 2-year warranty to a whopping 10-year warranty. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Brooks B72 Features and Retail</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $190</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Durable, 5mm vegetable-tanned leather</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Tubular steel rivets</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Distinctive side stamp</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Iconic Brooks backplate</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Springs for added comfort</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.brooksengland.com/en_us/\">BrooksEngland.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/brooks-b72-leather-spring-saddle-back-in-production/\">The Original Off-Road Adventure Saddle: Springy Brooks B72 is Back in Production</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"112d978c78d6adee09fddd13b92a1008a43de4cba429bfd79ef16d8c8c3eef5b","category":"Cycling"}